NEW INFORMATION: The USDA announced on August 31st a continuation of the Summer Food Service Program through 12/31/2020 allowing all meals to be offered free to all students.

Meal Qualifications:

All children between the ages of 1-18 are eligible for free meals. Children between the ages of 1-18 that are not enrolled in the USD 263 school district will be able to pick up meals from the Mulvane Middle School remote pick up site daily.

For more information visit the school food service pages

post_text:
The first day of school is almost here and Victor E. Wildcat is practicing the 3Ws. The 3Ws are the simple things everyone can do to help prevent the spread of COVID-19 whenever they leave the house, including:
‚Ä¢ WEAR a mask covering over your nose and mouth.
‚Ä¢ WATCH your distance. Stay 6 feet apart. Avoid close contact.
‚Ä¢ WASH your hands often with soap and water for at least 20 seconds or use hand sanitizer.

Families, please talk with your children about the importance of the 3Ws this school year and review the letter from our school nurses here: http://bit.ly/Nurse263

**We urge you to stay connected by checking school websites, your emails regularly and by watching district and building social media pages. USD 263 is committed to open, ongoing communication with students, staff, families and our community. We are communicating as much as possible to keep you informed and ready for the first few days and weeks of school!
We can't wait to see you!
#BeLikeVic #MaskUpMulvane #3Ws #StrongerTogether

post_text:
The Mulvane Board of Education voted last night to delay the start of the school for students until September 8th. A Task Force worked over the summer to make recommendations to the BOE on the best way to open schools.
This calendar change will give our educators additional time to collaborate and plan for the high quality instruction our teachers are known to provide students. It will also allow for health and safety protocols to be implemented in school buildings.
To help families navigate changes and next steps, we have created a link on our Mulvane Public Schools website that will go live tonight, July 28th at 6:00 PM. This link will provide more information about our plan for reopening schools, registration, learning options, and more.
Thanks for your continued support as we plan for the 2020-21 school year.

https://youtu.be/kfpfuLpz1fI

post_text:
Food service is starting tomorrow and we need your help!
Please take time to complete this short survey. We want to make sure we have enough meals for children ages 1-18 in our community.
Need to know:
1. Due to USDA mandates we are not allowed to distribute meals for any child that is NOT present at the pick up spot. Unfortunately, we cannot give meals to one child for all the children in one family. EACH child has to be present.
2. The child does not need to be enrolled in USD 263.
3. The child does not have to be on free/reduced lunch. Any child can participate in this program.
4. Please take this survey once per family and the survey is anonymous.

Link to Survey: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScr_zg8Kcjezjgh-PJlWT3nD06UhjqI1IKDSabohn1JxS7DCQ/viewform

Mulvane High School will be performing "The Addams Family" Musical Thursday 11/21, Friday 11/22, and Saturday 11/23 at 7:30 pm in the MHS auditorium. Tickets are $5 for adults and $3 for students. This is a PG show and children are welcome. The running time with one intermission is approximately two hours and forty-five minutes. The leading actors/actresses include Alyjah T, Mackenzie C, AJ G, Shelton L, Grace T, Jake R, Austin G, Anya M, and Mason O. There are over 85 students involved in the production between cast, crew, and pit who have been working since the beginning of September to produce this very entertaining show for you. We will also premier the use of digital projection backdrops which are animated and very exciting! Please join us! Contact Jason Mitchell jmitchell@usd263.org or Rachel Jansen rjansen@usd263.org to purchase tickets ahead of time or they will be sold at the door.

Mulvane Middle School
November 8, 2019 at 4:35 PM ¬∑

MMS came together today to kick off the annual Patriot League Food Drive. MMS STUCO sponsors the Food Drive so STUCO members, along with sponsors Ms. Mangas and Mrs. Grant, lead the school in an assembly of group chants and grade games. Last year, MMS placed 3rd, so this year, we're going for the gold! MMS can win the traveling trophy, and more importantly, MMS can help our friends at Care N Share, The Blessing Box, and the Mulvane PD (who will donate the food to families in need), so help us beat the perennial Food Drive winners, Ark City, this year! The Food Drive will start next week, November 11-15. STUCO will be collecting any nonperishable items and cash donations all next week. Help us help others. Go Cats!

Mulvane Public Library
November 6, 2019 at 6:37 PM ¬∑

We are loving fall and the beautiful colors that come with the season! Preschoolers read stories all about leaves today and got to do a fun leaf-rubbing art project. Such a simple but beautiful craft.

Want to do this craft at home? Go on a walk with your child(ren) and have them collect a few different kinds of leaves. Talk about their shapes, sizes, color, texture, etc. Then give them some paper and crayons (without the wrapper), put the leaves under the paper, and let them color over them to discover the images that pop through. Enjoy this wonderful time together exploring the beauty of fall!

Can you believe it's already October? That means it's time to start scheduling Munson conferences using Skyward Family Access. Teachers have set up 20 minute appointments to meet with parents from 4-730 PM on October 21 & 22 and 7:30-11 AM on October 24.

If you have already used Skyward Family Access to enroll, you are set to sign up for your Parent-Teacher conference. If you have not used Skyward Family Access yet, please contact LeAnn Pierce at 777-1102 or at lpierce@usd263.org to request your username and password. She'll be happy to help you set up your account.

*Log in to Skyward Family Access --> Choose your student to schedule --> Click the Conference button --> Press All Conferences --> Select a time that works for you.

Thank you for making time to team with us. We look forward to seeing you at conferences.
